    "abstract_prep": "This study aimed to evaluate clinical and microbiological effects of systemic azithromycin (systemic azithromycin) in adjunct to nonsurgical periodontal therapy (NSPT; or scaling root planing - SRP) in treatment of Aggregatibacter actinomycetemcomitans associated periodontitis (periodontitis). Seventy individuals with moderate to severe periodontitis and subgingival detection of A.\u00a0actinomycetemcomitans were randomly allocated to two groups. Thirty-five individuals were allocated to full mouth SRP+systemic azithromycin (500\u00a0mg oral delivery (SRP+AZM (500\u00a0mg oral delivery)\u00a0\u00d7\u00a03\u00a0days) while 35 individuals were allocated to SRP+Placebo (SRP+AZM (500\u00a0mg oral delivery\u00a0\u00d7\u00a03\u00a0days) group. The clinical variables evaluated were probing depth (depth), clinical attachment level (clinical attachment level), gingival index (gingival index), plaque index (plaque index), and percent bleeding on probing sites (%BOP), while microbiologic variables included percentage of subjects positive for A.\u00a0actinomycetemcomitans at baseline, 3, 6, and 12\u00a0months. The systemic azithromycin group showed statistically significant reduction in mean depth (2.91\u00a0\u00b1\u00a00.88\u00a0mm) as compared to placebo (1.51\u00a0\u00b1\u00a00.98\u00a0mm) (P\u00a0<\u00a00.001), while clinical attachment level gain was significant in the systemic azithromycin group (2.71\u00a0\u00b1\u00a01.15\u00a0mm) as compared to the placebo group (1.71\u00a0\u00b1\u00a01.29\u00a0mm) (P\u00a0<\u00a00.001). There was also a statistically significant reduction in the number of subjects positive for A.\u00a0actinomycetemcomitans in the systemic azithromycin group (P\u00a0<\u00a00.0001). Azithromycin was found to significantly improve the clinical and microbiological parameters in periodontitis individuals.",
